13:
I think I already look the part...
Actually... I should probably remove
the cloak, too.
23:
Hey, hey! What are you three up to?
Looks pretty serious!
27: Light... doesn't want to wear clothes!
37:
Phrasing, Stella! I simply said that I
do not need to wear this new outfit.
Not clothes in general!
41:
Oh, is this for the Voluntas Splice
ceremony? I mean, if Stella's getting
a new outfit... why not?
45:
As I said, I plan to serve as the
mascot for this event. It would be
best to appear as a soft, fluffy
animal, no?
49: That just doesn't sit right with me...
54:
It's not like you're dressing up either,
Alk. What's with that temper of yours?
58: Oh, please. I don't have a temper...
63:
Are you CERTAIN about that? What
of that one time, in the desert? Or
perhaps that time with Finn? I think
you very well do, Alk.
67:
But, seriously. You're not about to go
out there and bark or meow for the
crowd, are ya?
72:
And if not... Maybe it's not the best
idea to be naked?
76:
Wait. I hadn't considered that.
Without my cloak... would you think
me naked? That... cannot be right...
80:
No! Ridiculous! One does not call a
dog or a cat naked, do they?! But,
then again... I AM a human...
85:
I've actually talked to Mia and Sven
about this before and—
89:
All right. I've decided. I shall accept
the outfit you prepare. End of
conversation, no further questions!
93:
We just decided to agree that
people from different worlds have
their own way of doing thi—
98:
Did you not hear me?! Enough! My
species is fine like this!
110:
Hmm... I suppose this does have a
certain appeal.
114: Whoa! You look sooo cute, Lightsy!
119: Yeah! Er... Well, I mean it looks great!
128:
D-do you really think so? It feels a
tad TOO formal when the plan is to
get people to let their guard down...
133:
A-actually... Another shipment of
clothing has arrived from Heights
Couture. Maybe there's something
better—
139:
From Quazer?! Thank you, but no. I
will pass. Don't even open it.
142:
My archenemy... I just hope Arum
never finds out—
151:
Sir Light, please! When will you be
granting permission to nuzzle?!
156:
Have you no patience?! Calm
yourself! At least in front of everyo—
169:
Hold! No need to quarrel, everyone!
Try to remember that we are all
friends here!
177:
*sigh* A simple fitting was enough
to wear me out...
180:
Tell me, though... What did you call
me for? And why are you dressed up
as well?
184:
Heh-heh. Simple, my good chum.
When I heard there was need for an
escort for dear Stella—
187:
Ah... Speak no more. You intend to
annoy Alk, I see.
191:
Hahaha! I was shot down with a look
meant for rusted bolts in the
bargain bin!
195:
Some people never change. And
you... don't even try.
198:
Still... It is strange for Alk to deny a
call for aid in such a manner. Do you
want me to talk to him?
202:
Hey, now. Why would you be so cruel
as to take away that special bond
we have?
205: Special... bond? What do you mean?
210:
Alk's not the type to talk to just
anyone like that, y'know? He saves it
for a special few, like this guy here.
214:
And you... WANT him to continue
treating you like that?
219: There's no need to be jealous, pops.
223:
What reason would I have to be
jealous? Also... "pops?"
226:
...I admit I do tend to play the role of
guardian here and there, though
rarely by intention.
229:
Still, I believe Alk, Stella, and the
others can be entrusted with what's
important. That goes for both of you
as well.
234:
Heh... Sounds like you need a drink,
pal.
238:
...Not just yet. We have duties to
attend to at the ceremony.
242: Do you have what I requested, Regis?
247:
I've got the wiretap and camera
right here, see? I've got a direct line
to both. And you want that Suizen
boy similarly equipped, yes?
250:
We'll need them set up at Voluntas
Academy as well. Those will be the
decoys, placed where they are more
likely to be found.
255:
Well, well. Our high 'n mighty
Champion is taking a dip in the
shadows, huh?
259:
Any counterattack must be a
decisive one... Though of course, it
all depends on who our opponent
may be.
262:
I have already decided to do
everything I can.
